      },
      "date": "2013-06-15 17:57:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nRather than deleting these patches outright, for now please just change the comment at the top to say that they are not needed if CONFIG_FAIL_MAKE_REQUEST is enabled.  This will allow the code to continue testing if this option is not enabled in the kernel, and will allow the same kernel to be used for 2.1/2.4 Lustre to facilitate upgrades. \n\n The main osd_ro() code should check:\n\n #ifdef CONFIG_FAIL_MAKE_REQUEST\n         [stuff]\n #elif defined(HAVE_DEV_SET_RDONLY\n         [other stuff]\n #else\n         [complain]\n #endif\n\nIn some cases the \"stuff\" and \"other stuff\" can be the same. If the CONFIG_FAIL_MAKE_REQUEST code was wrapped in a little helper function like dev_fail_make_request() there could be a single #ifdef that wrapped the helper and selected whether to use the new or old code instead of putting all of the #ifdef inline in the code.\n\nSince CONFIG_FAIL_MAKE_REQUEST is not enabled by default in vendor kernels yet, we can't go over to this totally, but making it optional will get us half of the way.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
