        "subject": "LU-684 kernel: replace dev_rdonly with fault injection",
        "message": "LU-684 kernel: replace dev_rdonly with fault injection\n\nLustre has over time developed a method to simulate disk failures.\nThis approach requires you to patch your distribution kernel. Today\nthe linux kernel has a fault injection to simulate many types of\nfailures. This patch moves us over to this api to simulate failed\ndisks. The current dev_x_rdonly patches are kept for backwards\ncompatibility but if both are enabled fault injection will be used\ninstead of dev_x_rdonly. Most distros don't enable fault injection\nby default so keeping dev_x_rdonly helps ease this transition.\n\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\nChange-Id: I099b9112607b91eec2afd2a489e76804b47891de\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
